<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Spokane's B2B market context</h2>
<p class="body">Spokane's B2B ecosystem in 2026 is centered around healthcare tech, B2B SaaS, aerospace, agtech. For fractional CMO engagements specifically, this means:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Buyer rhythm matches the industries above — sales cycles, evaluation patterns, decision-maker profiles vary by sector</li>
<li>Talent market for senior fractional operators is meaningful — you have real options without paying coastal-tier rates</li>
<li>Most B2B buyers in Spokane want substance over hype — marketing/sales/finance that lands here translates well elsewhere</li>
<li>Pipeline rhythm rewards consistency more than peaks — quarterly cadence beats one-off campaigns</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Treetop's Spokane engagement model</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Remote-first with quarterly on-site.</strong> Quarterly in-person leadership offsites for Spokane engagements where scope warrants.</li>
<li><strong>1-2 days per week typical.</strong> Fractional means fractional — defined cadence, not always-on.</li>
<li><strong>Builder profile.</strong> We ship work; we don't just present strategy.</li>
<li><strong>AI-fluent.</strong> Modern fractional CMO work compounds with AI workflows. We bring those.</li>
<li><strong>12-18 month engagements</strong> typical for compounding outcomes.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Scope of work typically includes: strategy, positioning, demand generation, content, brand, team leadership.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to consider Treetop specifically</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You're a B2B founder/CEO at $3M-$30M ARR.</li>
<li>You're in Spokane or open to a remote-first engagement with quarterly on-site.</li>
<li>You want senior marketing leadership without a $300K+ full-time hire.</li>
<li>You want a fractional CMO who personally uses AI tooling, not just talks about it.</li>
<li>You can commit $8K-$25K/month for 12-18 months.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with companies in Spokane?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes. Treetop works remotely with B2B mid-market clients in Spokane and across Washington. In-person quarterly on-site available for Spokane-based clients when scope warrants.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Are you based in Spokane?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Treetop is based in Austin, TX. We work with clients across the US remotely with in-person quarterly on-site when warranted.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What's a typical fractional CMO engagement cost?</h3><p class="faq-qa">$8K-$25K/month depending on time commitment and scope. Typically 12-18 month engagements.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How do I start an engagement?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Book the $1,500 AI Audit as a low-commitment first engagement, or schedule a call directly.</p></div>
